  "prompt": "Where can I download free pdf books for mechanical engineering?",
  "response": "There are several websites where you can download free PDF books for mechanical engineering. Here's a list of some reliable sources:\n\n1. **Project Gutenberg** (www.gutenberg.org): While not specifically focused on technical books, Project Gutenberg offers over 60,000 free ebooks, many of which include works on mechanical engineering and related subjects.\n\n2. **Bookboon** (www.bookboon.com): Bookboon specializes in providing free textbooks for students. They have a range of mechanical engineering books that you can download as PDFs for free.\n\n3. **Internet Archive** (archive.org): The Internet Archive is a digital library with millions of free books, including many on engineering and technology.\n\n4. **Open Library** (openlibrary.org): The Open Library is part of the Internet Archive and offers access to many digitized books on mechanical engineering.\n\n5. **Library Genesis** (libgen.rs): Library Genesis is a file-sharing site that has many academic textbooks available for free download.\n\n6. **Free Engineering Books** (www.freeengineeringbooks.com): This site provides links to various free engineering books, including those focused on mechanical engineering.\n\nRemember to evaluate the legality of downloading from any website to ensure you respect copyright laws.",
